# Secrets/config live in DOPPLER (project: dnd), NOT in .env files.
#
# Local dev/build is wrapped with `doppler run` (see package.json scripts), so
# you normally don't need a .env file at all. Just run `bun run dev`.
#
# First-time setup on a new machine:
#   doppler login
#   doppler setup --project dnd --config dev
#
# The following variables are provided by Doppler and injected at build time.
# (They are public Firebase web-config values, exposed in the client bundle —
# access is controlled by Firebase Auth + Firestore rules, not by hiding them.)
#
#   VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY
#   VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN
#   VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID
#   VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET
#   VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID
#   VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID
#   VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID
#
# If you ever need to bypass Doppler locally, copy this file to `.env.local`
# and set the VITE_FIREBASE_* values directly (gitignored).
